.Dd 2026-07-06
.Dt graph 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm graph
.Nd CSR graph module with common graph algorithms
.Sh LIBRARY
IRIS C Library
.Pq Vt ilib_c
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
module implements
.Sy six graph flavors ,
all backed by CSR (compressed sparse row) adjacency storage, covering the undirected/directed and
unweighted/\fBint\fR-weighted/\fBfloat\fR-weighted combinations:
.Bl -tag -width "wfdgraph_t"
.It Sy graph_t
- undirected, unweighted
.It Sy dgraph_t
- directed, unweighted (fwd + reverse CSR)
.It Sy wigraph_t
- undirected, int-weighted
.It Sy wfgraph_t
- undirected, float-weighted
.It Sy widgraph_t
- directed, int-weighted (fwd + reverse CSR)
.It Sy wfdgraph_t
- directed, float-weighted (fwd + reverse CSR)
.El
.Pp
The corresponding structure definitions are:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *offsets;
	vertex_id_t *edges;

	graph_size_t vertex_count;
	graph_size_t edge_count;
} graph_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *offsets;
	vertex_id_t *edges;

	vertex_id_t *ioffsets;
	vertex_id_t *iedges;

	graph_size_t vertex_count;
	graph_size_t edge_count;
} dgraph_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *offsets;
	vertex_id_t *edges;
	int	    *weights;

	graph_size_t vertex_count;
	graph_size_t edge_count;
} wigraph_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *offsets;
	vertex_id_t *edges;
	int	    *weights;

	vertex_id_t *ioffsets;
	vertex_id_t *iedges;
	int	    *iweights;

	graph_size_t vertex_count;
	graph_size_t edge_count;
} widgraph_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *offsets;
	vertex_id_t *edges;
	float	    *weights;

	graph_size_t vertex_count;
	graph_size_t edge_count;
} wfgraph_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *offsets;
	vertex_id_t *edges;
	float	    *weights;

	vertex_id_t *ioffsets;
	vertex_id_t *iedges;
	float	    *iweights;

	graph_size_t vertex_count;
	graph_size_t edge_count;
} wfdgraph_t;
.Ed
.Pp
.Vt vertex_id_t
and
.Vt graph_size_t
are both aliases for
.Vt unsigned int .
.Ss Feature and Implementation Macros
Six configuration macros control linkage and allocation.
.Sy GRAPH_DECL
sets the linkage/inline specifier for every declaration
.Pq default : Sy static inline .
.Sy GRAPH_MALLOC , GRAPH_FREE , GRAPH_REALLOC ,
and
.Sy GRAPH_CALLOC
override the allocator; all four must be defined together, or none.
.Sy GRAPH_MEMSET
and
.Sy GRAPH_MEMCPY
override the mem ops; both or neither.
.Pp
Defining
.Sy GRAPH_IMPLEMENTATION
before including
.Nm
pulls in
.Xr queue 7
.Pq both Sy QUEUE_IMPLEMENTATION No and Sy PQUEUE_IMPLEMENTATION
and
.Xr dsetuf 7
.Pq Sy DSUF_IMPLEMENTATION ,
automatically, unless already defined, since
.Fn graph_bfs_al ,
.Fn wigraph_dijkstra_al ,
and
.Fn wigraph_kruskal_al
depend on them.
.Pp
The implementation also defines a set of sentinel macros used
throughout the traversal and shortest-path results, useful for callers
checking result values:
.Bl -tag
.It Sy I_VTX_UNVISITED
Sentinel value
.Pq Po Vt vertex_id_t Pc Ns \-1
marking a vertex as unvisited, unreachable, or lacking a predecessor
in DFS, BFS, and Floyd-Warshall next-hop results.
.It Sy I_DIJKSTRA_INT_INF
Sentinel
.Pq Dv 0x7fffffff
representing infinite distance in the integer-weighted Dijkstra and
Floyd-Warshall results.
.It Sy I_DIJKSTRA_FLT_INF
Sentinel
.Pq Dv 3.402823466e+38f ,
approximately
.Vt FLT_MAX ,
representing infinite distance in the float-weighted Dijkstra and
Floyd-Warshall results.
.It Sy I_FLOYD_UNREACHABLE
Alias for
.Sy I_VTX_UNVISITED ,
used in the Floyd-Warshall next-hop matrix to mark unreachable vertex
pairs.
.El
.Ss Memory ownership
Functions suffixed
.Sy _al
transfer ownership of every pointer in their result to the caller.
Free each with plain
.Fn free
.Pq or whatever Sy GRAPH_FREE No was configured as ,
never mixed with the graph's own destroy functions.
.Ss Construction and destruction
.Fn graph_construct , Fn dgraph_construct , Fn wigraph_construct , Fn wfgraph_construct ,
.Fn widgraph_construct ,
and
.Fn wfdgraph_construct
build a graph from an edge list. Undirected types internally double each
edge
.Pq Fa from , to
/
.Pq Fa to , from ;
directed types build both a forward and a reverse CSR.
.Pp
.Fn graph_destroy , Fn dgraph_destroy , Fn wigraph_destroy , Fn wfgraph_destroy ,
.Fn widgraph_destroy ,
and
.Fn wfdgraph_destroy
free all memory owned by the graph struct itself, not
.Sy _al
results.
.Ss Edge extraction
.Fn graph_edges_al , Fn dgraph_edges_al , Fn wigraph_edges_al , Fn widgraph_edges_al ,
.Fn wfgraph_edges_al ,
and
.Fn wfdgraph_edges_al
recover a flat, deduplicated (except for directed graphs) edge list from a graph's CSR storage.
.Pp
The following structures are the definitions of the edge types:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t from;
	vertex_id_t to;
} edge_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t from;
	vertex_id_t to;
	int	    weight;
} wedgei_t;

typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t from;
	vertex_id_t to;
	float	    weight;
} wedgef_t;
.Ed
.Ss Traversal
.Fn graph_dfs_al , Fn dgraph_dfs_al , Fn wigraph_dfs_al , Fn wfgraph_dfs_al ,
.Fn widgraph_dfs_al ,
and
.Fn wfdgraph_dfs_al
perform an iterative-recursive DFS over all components, reporting
per-vertex component id, a postorder vertex ordering, component count,
and whether any back-edge (cycle) was found.
.Pp
.Fn graph_bfs_al
and
.Fn dgraph_bfs_al
perform a BFS from a single origin, reporting visited flags, a
predecessor
.Pq Va prev
array, and distances in edge count.
.Pp
The result structures for these algorithms are defined as follows:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
typedef struct {
	vertex_id_t *component_id;
	vertex_id_t *postorder;
	graph_size_t component_count;
	char	     has_cycle;
} graph_dfs_result_t;

typedef struct {
	char 	     *visited;
	vertex_id_t  *prev;
	graph_size_t *dist;
	vertex_id_t   origin;
} graph_bfs_result_t;
.Ed
.Ss Shortest paths
.Fn wigraph_dijkstra_al , Fn widgraph_dijkstra_al , Fn wfgraph_dijkstra_al ,
and
.Fn wfdgraph_dijkstra_al
compute single-source shortest paths via a binary-heap priority queue.
Requires non-negative weights. Reports distances, predecessors, and
visited flags.
.Pp
.Fn wigraph_floyd_al , Fn widgraph_floyd_al , Fn wfgraph_floyd_al ,
and
.Fn wfdgraph_floyd_al
compute all-pairs shortest paths via Floyd-Warshall. Tolerates negative
edge weights
.Pq unlike Dijkstra
and flags negative cycles via
.Va has_negative_cycle .
Reports a flat
.Va n Ns * Ns Va n
distance matrix and a flat
.Va n Ns * Ns Va n
next-hop matrix for path reconstruction.
.Sy O(V^3)
time,
.Sy O(V^2)
space — mind the memory cost on large graphs.
.Pp
.Fn graph_floyd_path_al
walks a Floyd-Warshall next-hop matrix from one vertex to another,
returning the vertex sequence, or
.Dv NULL
if unreachable.
.Pp
The result structures for these algorithms are defined as follows:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
typedef struct {
	int         *dist;
	vertex_id_t *prev;
	char        *visited;
	vertex_id_t  origin;
} graph_dijkstra_i_result_t;

typedef struct {
	float       *dist;
	vertex_id_t *prev;
	char        *visited;
	vertex_id_t  origin;
} graph_dijkstra_f_result_t;

typedef struct {
	int          *dist;
	vertex_id_t  *next;
	graph_size_t  vertex_count;
	char          has_negative_cycle;
} graph_floyd_i_result_t;

typedef struct {
	float        *dist;
	vertex_id_t  *next;
	graph_size_t  vertex_count;
	char          has_negative_cycle;
} graph_floyd_f_result_t;
.Ed
.Ss Minimum spanning tree
.Fn wigraph_kruskal_al
and
.Fn wfgraph_kruskal_al
compute a minimum spanning tree via edge-sorted priority queue and
disjoint-set union
.Pq Xr dsetuf 7 .
Reports the MST edge list and total span weight. Undirected, int and
float weight variants only.
.Pp
The result structures for these algorithms are defined as follows:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
typedef struct {
	int           span_weight;
	wedgei_t     *MST;
	graph_size_t  mst_size;
} graph_kruskal_i_result_t;

typedef struct {
	float         span_weight;
	wedgef_t     *MST;
	graph_size_t  mst_size;
} graph_kruskal_f_result_t;
.Ed
